# Shell + Python tooling must stay LF: these run under bash (incl. Windows/Git Bash,
# where CRLF makes bash fail with `$'\r': command not found`) and the skill templates
# are copied verbatim into consumer projects, so a CRLF commit would ship CRLF scripts.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
.agents/tools/*.sh text eol=lf
.agents/tools/hooks/*.sh text eol=lf
.agents/tools/*.py text eol=lf
.agents/tools/hooks/*.py text eol=lf
.agents/relink-skills.sh text eol=lf
.agents/*.py text eol=lf
